article.description: Montana State routs Black Hills State 57-10
article.headline: Montana State routs Black Hills State 57-10
article.linkText: Montana State routs Black Hills State 57-10
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. -- Dakota Prukop threw two touchdown passes and ran for three more to lead Montana State to a 57-10 rout Saturday night of Division II Black Hills State. In the first 8:12, Prukop ran for a 60-yard touchdown and connected with Justin Paige for a 43-yard score. Prukop had touchdown runs of 57 and 6 yards, and hit Tanner Roderick with a 33-yard strike in the second quarter. Gunnar Brekke ran for a 1-yard touchdown to open the fourth quarter and cap the scoring for Montana State. The Bobcats (1-1) had 637 yards of total offense, the most since recording 646 against Sacramento State in 2010. Phydell Paris had 12 carries for 76 yards and a 49-yard touchdown run to lead Black Hills State (0-1). It was the first meeting between the schools.
